  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Water Well Rehabilitation &amp; Hygiene Education</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Water for South Sudan (WFSS) rehab team will repair older wells, using newer design and specifications. Villagers will be responsible for wells upon completion, and must provide villagers willing to be trained in maintenance and upkeep of the well.

WFSS Hygiene Team will travel with the rehab team and train eight people in each village (four men and four women) to improve hygiene practices. Activities include education in how germs spread, keeping cooking areas and utensils clean, and will also focus on personal hygiene.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Water for South Sudan will rehabilitate up to 20 of its older wells, using data obtained from 2015 monitoring &amp;amp; evaluation trip. WFSS hygiene team will provide hygiene education in every village where a well is repaired.</narrative>
  </description>
